		</h4><div class="row"><div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-2">Reihe:</div><div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-10">de Gruyter Lehrbuch</div></div><div class="row"><div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-2">Verlag:</div><div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-10">De Gruyter</div></div><div class="row"><div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-2">Seiten:</div><div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-10">xii+281 pages</div></div><div><a class="external-link" target="_blank" href="http://www.degruyter.com/view/product/43233">Link zur Publikation</a></div></div></div><div class="entry" id="employee-pub-279"><p><span class="publication-first-line pub-279">2000 | <i>Dirac eigenvalues and total scalar curvature</i> | Bernd Ammann, Christian Bär</span><span class="publication-detail-row"><span class="publication-detail">Zeitschrift: J. Geom. Phys.</span><span class="publication-detail">Verlag: Elsevier</span><span class="publication-detail">Seiten: 229-234</span><span class="publication-detail">Band: 33, no.3-4</span></span><a class="external-link" target="_blank" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0393-0440(99)00050-9">Link zur Publikation</a>
